# CODEOWNERS — require an owner's review before any path that could turn a
# REQUIRED CI check into a no-op is changed.
#
# A workflow cannot protect against edits to ITSELF (a PR runs the PR's own copy),
# so the enforcing boundary is GitHub repo governance: branch protection + required
# CODEOWNERS review on these paths (see docs/COURSE_MAINTENANCE.md → "CI integrity /
# branch protection"). This covers each required check AND its implementation
# closure — the workflow, the helper scripts, the activation marker, the code a
# gate/check executes, AND the dependency/bootstrap config that controls how the
# checks build and run (an install lifecycle script or build hook can rewrite a
# gate impl during install) — so a PR cannot neutralise a check without an owner's
# review. Replace @starkyru with the maintainer team if this moves to an org
# (e.g. @org/course-maintainers).

# The entire CI/automation surface (workflows, actions config).
/.github/                             @starkyru

# The CI helper scripts (control-char scan, smoke wiring, eval-gate status).
/scripts/ci/                          @starkyru

# The curriculum-QA + smoke-runner implementation (check_structure, manifest,
# build_manifest, smoke_exercises, net_guard) that the `curriculum` and `smoke`
# required checks execute — and the eval-gate activation marker.
/scripts/curriculum/                  @starkyru

# The 21b release-gate implementation closure (py/gate.py, ts/gate-cli.ts, and
# everything the gate imports) that the required `eval-gate` job runs — so the
# gate cannot be replaced with an exit-0 no-op while the marker stays active.
/modules/21b-evaluation-reliability/  @starkyru

# The dependency/bootstrap + build config: install lifecycle scripts, lockfiles,
# and build backends decide what code runs during `pnpm install` / `uv sync` and
# how the checks compile/run — a hook here could rewrite a gate impl unreviewed.
/package.json                            @starkyru
/pnpm-lock.yaml                          @starkyru
/pnpm-workspace.yaml                     @starkyru
/pyproject.toml                          @starkyru
/uv.lock                                 @starkyru
/tsconfig.json                           @starkyru
/jest.config.mjs                         @starkyru
/packages/py/llm_core/pyproject.toml     @starkyru
